    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Palestinian Children</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael J Jordan letter responds to Oct 23 editorial; questions why, if Israelis are murdering Palestinian children as Palestinian leaders claim, Palestinian parents continue to allow their children into the streets, particularly onto front line of the confrontation (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Among the many puzzling issues in the Middle East conflict (editorial, Oct. 23), perhaps someone can answer this: If, as many of the Palestinian leaders say, the Israelis are murdering Palestinian children, why do Palestinian parents continue to allow their children into the streets, particularly onto the front lines of the confrontation?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Among the many puzzling issues in the Middle East conflict (editorial, Oct. 23), perhaps someone can answer this: If, as many of the Palestinian leaders say, the Israelis are murdering Palestinian children, why do Palestinian parents continue to allow their children into the streets, particularly onto the front lines of the confrontation?</p>
        <p>After all, I haven't seen any reports saying children and young adults are being shot and killed in their homes, schools or mosques. Only in the streets, amid confrontation with Israeli security forces. Is martyrdom that powerful a force?</p>
        <p>MICHAEL J. JORDAN  New York, Oct. 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
